<TITLE> Fire guts cinema hall in Sherpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sherpur, June 15 (bdnews24.com) -- A devastating fire swept through a cinema hall on Sherpur's Bulbul Road early Friday. Golam Kibria Liton, one of the owners of the Padma Cinema Hall, said the blaze had destroyed assets worth Tk 25 lakh. He told bdnews24.com that the blaze broke out at 7am in the operating room of the hall and spread throughout the building rapidly. The blaze lasted two hours, reducing the building to ashes. All equipment and furniture were lost. Firefighters were able to bring the fire under control by 9 am. An official with the Fire Service and Civil Defence said the blaze might have started after an electrical malfunctioning. bdnews24
